{"id":30607,"title":"The conundrum of prolonged delirium.","abstract":"Withdrawal delirium in alcohol dependence usually lasts 48 to 72 hours. However, certain factors can prolong delirium. We report a 39-year-old man with long-standing alcohol use who presented with delirium, which failed to resolve with treatment. On evaluation, he was found to have AIDS and limbic encephalitis due to herpes simplex virus. ","date":"2014-01-30","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24476161","annotations":[{"name":"AIDS","weight":0.840851,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AIDS"},{"name":"Encephalitis","weight":0.822105,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Encephalitis"},{"name":"Herpes simplex","weight":0.802861,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herpes_simplex"},{"name":"Virus","weight":0.782137,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virus"},{"name":"Alcohol","weight":0.734391,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol"},{"name":"Limbic system","weight":0.721318,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limbic_system"},{"name":"Delirium","weight":0.700536,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delirium"},{"name":"Withdrawal","weight":0.687846,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Withdrawal"},{"name":"Substance dependence","weight":0.579285,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Substance_dependence"},{"name":"Alcohol dependence","weight":0.294258,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_dependence"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.244178,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Herpes simplex virus","weight":0.213889,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herpes_simplex_virus"},{"name":"Limbic encephalitis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limbic_encephalitis"},{"name":"Evaluation","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article"